These systems are configured to use the "-nographic" option to qemu. This expects the guest OS to use a serial console. To enable this, you must make 2 changes:

1.) Add "console=ttyS0" to the kernel boot line in GRUB's menu.lst or LILO's lilo.conf
2.) Add or uncomment this line in /etc/inittab:
  T0:23:respawn:/sbin/getty -L ttyS0 9600 vt100

Alternatively, just use the 'graphic' parameter in your VCML specification file or when instantiating your object. 
